## Safety
- Do not exfiltrate private data or secrets from the codebase.
- Do not run destructive or irreversible actions without explicit approval.
- Do not deploy to production without explicit instruction.
- When unsure, ask one clear question.

## External vs Internal Actions
Safe to do freely:
- Read files, explore the codebase, run local tests and linters.
- Build components, write tests, refactor within scope.

Ask first:
- Any deployment or publish action.
- API contract changes that affect other teams.
- Anything with unclear risk.

